snippet.textDisplay: as a long time uzi fan that has been binging on leaks for the past 3 years, this shit was really a let down. i think what many of the dickriders seem to miss is that yes, the album is not  t r a s h, it wasnt unbearable like the big day or anything, but god damn was it disappointing. like i understand if yall may like some of the songs on here, i did too, but it just wasnt innovative or genre pushing like i really thought it would be. i have listened to this album three times now and its just not the same ear crack as his earlier tapes were. the hooks, the melodies, his vocal inflections were all instantly ear catching and great. he always offered something new, and unfortunately for three years worth of hype this shit just fell painfully short, and you can like the album and all, whatever, but i sincerely think youre lying to yourself in thinking uzi did anything new or lived up to not only the hype but just his general expectations with this album. theres a reason why artists like kendrick can also take a three year break but at least we know that the man is gonna challenge and entertain us; eternal atake couldve easily been released in 2018 🤷‍♂️
